cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the development of a predictive display for teleoperated surgical robots. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper utilizes Augmented Reality (AR) to show the predicted motions alongside the complex tissue found in-situ within surgical environments. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category as the paper discusses the development of a stereoscopic display. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper conducted a user study to test the SARPD's performance. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of AR and stereoscopic display to show complex surgical environments.
